<p><em><strong>The size of <a href="https://www.verifiedmarketreports.com/download-sample/?rid=752358&utm_source=GitHub&utm_medium=285" target="_blank">Calcitriol Injection Market </a> was estimated to be worth USD Calcitriol Injection Market billion in 2023 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of xxx% to reach USD Calcitriol Injection Market billion by 2030.</strong></em><br /><h2>Global Calcitriol Injection Market by Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) Application</h2><p>Calcitriol injections are widely used in the management of chronic kidney disease (CKD), particularly in patients who develop secondary hyperparathyroidism due to the condition. CKD often leads to an impaired ability to convert vitamin D into its active form, resulting in low calcium levels in the blood. This imbalance stimulates the parathyroid glands to release excess parathyroid hormone (PTH), which in turn can cause bone disorders and cardiovascular issues. Calcitriol, the active form of vitamin D, helps to regulate calcium levels and suppress the overproduction of PTH, preventing the progression of bone disease and other complications associated with CKD. As a result, calcitriol injections have become an essential therapeutic option for CKD patients.</p><p>The rising prevalence of chronic kidney disease worldwide, particularly driven by the growing incidence of diabetes and hypertension, is fueling the demand for calcitriol injections in clinical settings. Patients undergoing dialysis often rely on calcitriol injections to manage their mineral and bone disorder, as oral forms of the drug may not be as effective due to gastrointestinal absorption issues. As the global population ages and the burden of CKD continues to increase, the application of calcitriol injections in this field is expected to grow, supporting market expansion in the healthcare sector.</p><h2>Global Calcitriol Injection Market by Hypocalcemia Application</h2><p>Hypocalcemia, or low calcium levels in the blood, is another significant condition treated with calcitriol injections. This condition can arise due to various causes, including post-surgical hypoparathyroidism, vitamin D deficiency, and critical illness. Calcitriol injections are used to rapidly elevate calcium levels in the bloodstream, especially in patients who cannot absorb vitamin D efficiently through the digestive system. The injectable form ensures direct and immediate therapeutic action, which is crucial in severe cases of hypocalcemia, such as those occurring post-thyroidectomy or in critically ill patients with acute hypocalcemia.</p><p>In addition to its use in emergency settings, calcitriol injections are also employed in long-term management of hypocalcemia in patients with chronic conditions that affect calcium metabolism. For instance, individuals with genetic disorders like hypoparathyroidism or those with impaired renal function often require ongoing calcitriol therapy to maintain stable calcium levels. As awareness of hypocalcemia-related health risks grows and diagnostic practices improve, the demand for calcitriol injections in the management of both acute and chronic forms of the condition is expected to rise, contributing to the global market's growth.</p></p><p id="" class=""><strong>Download Full PDF Sample Copy of Reseach Report @ <a target="">https://www.verifiedmarketreports.com/download-sample/?rid=752358&utm_source=GitHub&utm_medium=285</a></strong></p><h3 id="" class="">Who is the largest manufacturers of&nbsp;Calcitriol Injection Market worldwide?</h3><h3 class=""></Li><Li>Abbott</Li><Li> Akorn Pharmaceuticals</Li><Li> Abbvie</Li><Li> NEPHRX</Li><Li> LLC</Li><Li> Fresenius Kabi</Li><Li> Sterimax Inc</Li><Li> AMERICAN REGENT</Li><Li> INC</Li><Li> Teva Parenteral Medicines</Li><Li> Gland Pharma Limited</h3><h3 id="" class="">Calcitriol Injection Market &nbsp;Segments Analysis</h3><p id="" class="">Using a deliberate segmentation strategy, the Calcitriol Injection Market resear